<h2><span id="Rate.E2.80.93distortion_functions"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Rate–distortion_functions">Rate–distortion functions</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Rate%E2%80%93distortion_theory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Rate–distortion functions">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The functions that relate the rate and distortion are found as the solution of the following minimization problem:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \inf _{Q_{Y\mid X}(y\mid x)}I_{Q}(Y;X){\text{ subject to }}D_{Q}\leq D^{*}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <munder>
          <mo movablelimits="true" form="prefix">inf</mo>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <msub>
              <mi>Q</mi>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi>Y</mi>
                <mo>&#x2223;<!-- ∣ --></mo>
                <mi>X</mi>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
            <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
            <mi>y</mi>
            <mo>&#x2223;<!-- ∣ --></mo>
            <mi>x</mi>
            <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
          </mrow>
        </munder>
        <msub>
          <mi>I</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>Q</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>Y</mi>
        <mo>;</mo>
        <mi>X</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mtext>&#xA0;subject to&#xA0;</mtext>
        </mrow>
        <msub>
          <mi>D</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>Q</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>&#x2264;<!-- ≤ --></mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>D</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>&#x2217;<!-- ∗ --></mo>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \inf _{Q_{Y\mid X}(y\mid x)}I_{Q}(Y;X){\text{ subject to }}D_{Q}\leq D^{*}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e9c044b2c371a902524be2693b0b32c44568adc2" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.838ex; width:38.195ex; height:4.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \inf _{Q_{Y\mid X}(y\mid x)}I_{Q}(Y;X){\text{ subject to }}D_{Q}\leq D^{*}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>Here <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle Q_{Y\mid X}(y\mid x)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi>Q</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>Y</mi>
            <mo>&#x2223;<!-- ∣ --></mo>
            <mi>X</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mo>&#x2223;<!-- ∣ --></mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle Q_{Y\mid X}(y\mid x)}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b3098ccf207caea924987c1cd4c86d9dc2bb6073" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.171ex; width:11.414ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle Q_{Y\mid X}(y\mid x)}"></span>, sometimes called a test channel, is the <a href="/wiki/Conditional_probability" title="Conditional probability">conditional</a> <a href="/wiki/Probability_density_function" title="Probability density function">probability density function</a> (PDF) of the communication channel output (compressed signal) <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle Y}">
  <semantics>
