</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7cde9d54630c2425deeec9410a7eeca860acf8c9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:9.563ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle H(Y\mid X)}"></span> are the entropy of the output signal <i>Y</i> and the <a href="/wiki/Conditional_entropy" title="Conditional entropy">conditional entropy</a> of the output signal given the input signal, respectively:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle H(Y)=-\int _{-\infty }^{\infty }P_{Y}(y)\log _{2}(P_{Y}(y))\,dy}">
